{
  "texts": [
    "The unencoded magic state prepared directly on two physical qubits gives an average (avg.)",
    "infidelity across 28 qubit pairs as approximately 6.2 × 10 -2 (green dashed line) using 18 repetitions over a 24-h period with 10 5 shots per circuit.",
    "Of these, the best-performing pair yields a minimum (min.)",
    "infidelity of (2.354 ± 0.271) × 10 -2 (red solid line) found over all repetitions for all qubit pairs.",
    "In all cases, the error-suppressed scheme exceeds the fidelity of the best two-qubit unencoded magic state."
  ]
}